#: ../retro_games_console.rst:44
msgid "Game System Installation"
msgstr ""

#: ../retro_games_console.rst:46
msgid ""
"RetroPie allows you to turn your Raspberry Pi, ODroid C1/C2, or PC into a"
" retro-gaming machine. It builds upon Raspbian OS, Emulation Station, "
"RetroArch and many other projects to enable you to play your favorite "
"Arcade, home-console, and classic PC games with the minimum set-up."
msgstr ""

#: ../retro_games_console.rst:52
msgid "Installing **RetroPie**:"
msgstr ""

#: ../retro_games_console.rst:54
msgid ""
"**Step 1**: Download the SD image compatible with the Raspberry Pi 4 on "
"the `RetroPie official website <https://retropie.org.uk/>`_."
msgstr ""

#: ../retro_games_console.rst:61
msgid ""
"**Step 2**: After the download is complete, unzip the downloaded package "
"containing the image file."
msgstr ""

#: ../retro_games_console.rst:63
msgid "**Step 3**ï¼šThen flash the RetroPie image into the micro-SD card."
msgstr ""

#: ../retro_games_console.rst:65
msgid ""
"For Windows, use: `Raspberry Pi Imager "
"<https://www.raspberrypi.org/software/>`_, `Etcher "
"<https://www.balena.io/etcher/>`_, or `Win32DiskImager "
"<https://sourceforge.net/projects/win32diskimager/>`_."
msgstr ""

#: ../retro_games_console.rst:69
msgid ""
"Win32DiskImager requires an .img file extracted from the .img.gz image "
"downloaded in step 2. You can use a program like 7zip to do this."
msgstr ""

#: ../retro_games_console.rst:71
msgid ""
"For macOS, use: `Raspberry Pi Imager "
"<https://www.raspberrypi.org/software/>`_, `Etcher "
"<https://www.balena.io/etcher/>`_, `Apple Pi Baker "
"<https://www.tweaking4all.com/software/macosx-software/macosx-apple-pi-"
"baker/>`_, or the dd command."
msgstr ""

#: ../retro_games_console.rst:72
msgid ""
"For Linux, use: `Raspberry Pi Imager "
"<https://www.raspberrypi.org/software/>`_, `Etcher "
"<https://www.balena.io/etcher/>`_, or the dd command"
msgstr ""

#: ../retro_games_console.rst:76
msgid ""
"MacOS/Linux users can optionally extract the .img image from the "
"downloaded .img.gz by using gunzip (macOS users can also simply double-"
"click it)."
msgstr ""

#: ../retro_games_console.rst:82
msgid ""
"**Step 4**: Insert the micro-SD card into the RasPad, and press the power"
" button to boot up the system."
msgstr ""

#: ../retro_games_console.rst:86
msgid ""
"The SD card slot is a snap-in style attached to the back cover. Before "
"removing or replacing the back cover, remove the micro-SD card to avoid "
"damaging the micro-SD card and the RasPad's internal button board."
msgstr ""

